Description: Ostracon, small fragment of a red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and faint traces of three lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393796) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393796)
